    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="125"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/3263½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Swiss Minister</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RDP1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ritter</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d125fn1">Transmitted under the following covering letter of
                        same date: “My dear Mr. Secretary: Mr. <persName corresp="#p_PFL1"
                            >Polk</persName> expressed this morning the desire that I shall send you
                        a memorandum concerning the conversation I have had with him yesterday
                        evening. Please find same herewith enclosed.”</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Swiss Government has been requested by the German Government to say that the
                    latter is, now as before, willing to negotiate, formally or informally, with the
                    United States, provided that the commercial blockade against England will not be
                    broken thereby.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 11, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
